--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ADOBE EXPERIENCE MANAGER

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job description 1 : 
As a DAM AEM Expert, you will be responsible for implementing, managing, and optimizing Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) for our digital asset management needs. 
You will work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to enhance user experiences, streamline workflows, and ensure the efficient use of digital assets in the cloud environment. 
Your expertise in both front-end and back-end development will be essential for customizing AEM functionalities and integrations.
Collaborate with UX/UI designers to develop user-friendly interfaces for asset
Management.
Use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to customize AEM front-end components and templates.
Develop and maintain AEM workflows and custom services using Java and Sling models.
Integrate AEM with other systems and platforms, ensuring seamless data flow.
Manage AEM instances in cloud environments (e.g., Azure).
Implement cloud-based solutions to enhance scalability and performance.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 2 : 
Develop and maintain AEM components, templates, and workflows.
Implement AEM solutions including content management, personalization, and integrations with third-party systems.
Customize and extend AEM functionalities using Java, Sling, OSGi, and JCR.
Work closely with UI/UX designers to implement responsive, user-friendly web applications.
Optimize AEM performance and scalability.
Troubleshoot and resolve AEM-related issues.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including content authors, marketers, and backend developers.
Follow best practices for AEM development, including code reviews, version control, and deployment processes.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 3 : 
AEM certification is a plus.
Experience with cloud-based AEM solutions (AEM as a Cloud Service).
Exposure to Adobe Analytics, Adobe Target, or other Adobe Marketing Cloud tools.
Experience: 3+ years of AEM development experience.
Technical Skills:
Strong proficiency in Adobe Experience Manager (AEM 6.5 or later).
Experience with OSGi, Apache Sling, JCR, and Sightly/HTL.
Strong Java development skills, including servlets and REST APIs.
Frontend experience with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and frameworks like React or Angular is a plus.
Knowledge of AEM workflows, dispatcher configurations, and caching mechanisms.
Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines, Git, Maven, and Jenkins.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 4 : 
Experience :: 5+ Years of relevant experience
Location :: Bangalore

Required Qualifications:
5 years of experience developing solutions Adobe Experience Manager with knowledge of Templates, Layouts, components, APIs (OSGI)
4+ years of experience of working on Adobe Launch Products.
Experience with AEM 6.4 / 6.5
Demonstrated experience with Java, JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3 and related technologies
Experience collaborating with a variety of stakeholders and colleagues
Experience and desire to work within a fast-paced, iterative development environment, experience with Agile a strong plus
Ability to write complex programs, analyze code changes and make suggestions to improve code complexity for maintainability and scalability.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 5 : 
Proven experience with Adobe Experience Manager (AEM).
 Strong understanding of content repositories (JCR).
 Proficiency in Java and JSP for building custom AEM components.
 Expertise in HTL (formerly Sightly), Sling models, OSGi services, and Sling
Servlet.
 Experience with build tools such as Maven.
 Familiarity with front-end technologies, including HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript,
and libraries like jQuery.
 Experience in content migration.
 Proficiency with version control systems, such as Git.
 Experience working in Agile development environments.
